answers.q: e309-16 what kind of welding rod
answers.a: As a food additive, E309 is delta-tocopherol (a vitamin E antioxidant); “E309-16” is a welding electrode designation and is unrelated to food additives.

answers.q: in what foods are delta tocopherol
answers.a: It occurs naturally in vegetable oils (especially soybean, corn, and canola) and in nuts and seeds. When used as an additive (E309), it stabilizes fats in products like cooking oils, margarines/shortenings, salad dressings, snacks, and fat‑rich baked goods.
